WRITING.TEXT:
b'Well the most important thing is for her to get to a stable and secure place. This usually takes a very long time, in my case as I said it was over 3 months. Then when she comes off mania she might take a while to realise what she did was wrong, and by then I don't know if you'll want to take her back again. It's a tough situation. As a bipolar person it's kind of hard to process what you did when manic, as there's memory loss attached to it. Also I personally feel that I cannot be held accountable for what I did because "it wasn't really me"... so yeah you will probably want her to apologise as you will have been waiting for her to come back and she probably won't apologise. 

But yes there is a possibility she might want to get back together when she's not manic. 

I think you should try to focus on how to get her help. See if there are any local resources you can use, hotlines you can call, etc.'

b'Can you guys try to be kinder on this subreddit? Literally all the posts i have been reading here are just complaining about your SOs with bipolar and doing very little effort to understand the pain we face or what it is like to go through the ups and downs of bipolar.

What you are describing here is very normal bipolar behaviour. She probably needs her meds adjusted and medical help. If you know her family, i advise you talk to them and inform them of the situation so they can bring her to hospital. 

The fact that she left and is now behaving differently is probably because she might be rapid cycling. I don't know man it feels sort of wrong that you say "I don't know her anymore" or "this isn't what I signed up for"... this is very typical bipolar disorder behaviour and when someone is in the throes of mania you can't hold them accountable because they literally cannot think rationally.'

WRITING.TEXT:
b"Okay, first things first: I love speaking in English and whenever someone international approaches me I don't hesitate to switch languages and speak in English. I am a professional translator so it's not a big deal to me and I am happy to make other people feel comfortable.

However, I do feel that plenty of people are coming to the city with the intention of stating and they don't even bother to learn a single word. I think it is honestly quite disrespectful towards the place you're choosing to stay in and the people who live there. 

Keep in mind that catalan was prohibited in schools by Franco and has suffered a lot of repression. It is up to us Catalans to keep it alive and healthy. We don't want to let it die out like Irish...

So all in all... I want to make foreigners feel welcome yet I want them to understand that if they want to spend long periods of time here, they should learn the language. Out of basic respect and decency."

WRITING.TITLE: b'how do you deal with memory lapses?'
WRITING.TEXT:
b'So today I was talking to my brother and he reminded me of something that happened during one of my depressive episodes, it had to do with a mechanism we used to avoid confrontation and sensitive topics for me. What shocked me is that I could barely remember any of it... I felt so powerless and stupid not remembering anything. I guess my brain blocked it out because it was traumatic but I kinda of hate not being able to recall anything and it kind of removes my sense of agency or of "owning" my past and my story.

In the past my psychiatrist told me i would not remember anything from my manic episode and that it was better off this way. But i think I disagree. I want to find out more, I want to know everything. I don't know why , maybe it's morbid curiosity but after all it's my life, isn't it?

How do you guys feel about this?'

WRITING.TITLE: b"My friend doesn't want to be friends anymore because he's got a girlfriend now"
WRITING.TEXT:
b"Okay so me and this guy let's call him Fernando met in a mental health hospital where we both shared pretty intense crazy experiences to say the least. At first we were friends but then we had a short relationship which lasted around a month. After that we became friends again and we didn't really have anything romantic going on and we would have sex very very very sporadically. There were no romantic feelings though.

As mentally ill people, we both appreciate it having someone that understands what it's like to suffer from this sort of conditions. He has expressed how much he appreciates me and my friendship multiple times.

However in the past month he has told me that he now has a girlfriend. I completely understood and of course wasn't going to engage in sexual activities with him anymore. He told me that he wanted to still be friends and that it would be okay and that he appreciates me.

Anyway time went on and it seems that this girlfriend is not comfortable with us being friends and she has made it clear to Fernando that she's not happy that he has me as a friend given the fact that I'm his ex. He told me that and I sort of insisted that he should be able to make his own choices and that she should understand and trust him. He thought about it and said that what I was saying was reasonable and then then we could continue to be friends.

However today he has texted me that he needs to distance himself from me because her girlfriend doesn't want us to be friends anymore and that it is his priority to keep his girlfriend.

Of course, I think I deeply believe that this is wrong and that a good person who loves you will not try to limit who your friends are no matter what especially since you're promising that nothing's going to happen. But am I wrong to think this way? 

My instincts in this instance would be to try to convince him that she's wrong and that he's giving in and losing a friend... but at the same time I am tired I'm tired of fighting for our friendship and he's seemingly not willing to fight for me... should I just ignore him and block him everywhere?

What do you think? I am very lost at this point.


TLDR: my friend with whom I had a short relationship has a new girlfriend and she doesn't want him to have any contact with me because of our history. Should I insist that we remain friends or should I just let him go and tell him to f*** off because he's not willing to fight for our friendship like I have so far?"

WRITING.TITLE: b'Can I safely come off meds for Bipolar Disorder (Type 1)'
WRITING.TEXT:
b"F26 here. Diagnosed over a year ago with bipolar disorder type 1 with bouts of severe depression nearing suicide and mania with vivid delusions and insomnia which resulted in psych ward stays.

I have always taken my prescribed meds (lithium and depakine) and I have been gaining a lot of weight, up to 20 kg now. I am very unhappy about this. I also am quite flat and feel like I'm on a sort of limbo, not happy, not sad.

I also dislike the idea of having to take meds for life, which is what my psychiatrist envisions for me.


So, doctors, in your experience, is it possible to treat bipolar disorder differently? Can one just take the medicine as needed, when one feels like an episode is coming,  rather than having to take meds every day for the rest of your life?


Thank you in advance!"

Tips are welcome!'

WRITING.TEXT: b'Yes well the most important thing is the Message. No missing information on the target text. You also need to take into account who your target readers are and whether they are similar to the ones the original text was intended for. You also need to know what kind of translation the client expects. Is he fussy about keeping the overall style of the author? Does he want the translation to be fully adapted and idiomatic for the target audience? Are there any cultural terms that you might need to explain further? Is there any specific previous knowledge or terminology you need to be aware of? Are there any conventions as to how the type of text you are translating is usually formatted? Are there any software tools that might make your job easier (knowledge about CAT tools is key if you want to be consistent and efective)... There is a lot to cover, a course would not hurt.'

WRITING.TITLE: b' '
WRITING.TEXT: b'Yes definitely. They provided me with the right medicine to get through the psychotic episode and my depression, they looked after me and cared for me 24/7 for two weeks. It was a bit like a prison but I needed to be there as I was a danger to myself and others.'

WRITING.TITLE: b' '
WRITING.TEXT: b"I mean interesting... It was interesting. Hell but interesting. I was convinced everyone around me was involved in a sort of plot against me, which was led by the government. All medical professionals were actors. I thought everything I was living had already happened before, like a weird dejavu. I was really freaked out by machines or electrical stuff. I don't remember much else aside from that. It was a strange time. \n\nI think the most interesting thing was not being able to trust my own judgement. After my psychotic episode I was no longer sure if my thoughts were real and reasonable or some strange delusion."

WRITING.TITLE: b' '
WRITING.TEXT: b"Hey! Well it's hard to get someone in full blown psychosis to go to the hospital to be fair. I personally was convinced that all the doctors were actors. It is impossible to reason with someone who's at that stage. Nothing will help. So yeah my advice is to prevent that person from reaching that stage, however that may be. Taking meds is important. Mine were Olanzapine and they did help with the delusions but they had quite a lot of side effects, one of them being they leave you quite drowsy and sleepy. My advice is, when they are still being reasonable, try to make them see that hospitalisation might help them. As for help when they are inside, board games are fun. But just be careful they don't contain any piece of glass. They don't let us have anything with glass that could potentially be used for self harm. Also if the person is artsy, some art supplies would be nice. In my ward we'd paint mandalas and things like that. We'd also make bracelets. \n\nIt's alright, I'm a lot better now. Thanks for reaching out! You sound like such a good support person."

La meva pagina web







 Julia Moll Cerda

 

 Sobre mi 

 Us explicare una mica la meva vida, per posar-vos en context. Vaig neixer a Barcelona l'octubre de l'any 1995, la qual cosa em fa del signe del zodiac libra, pero aquestes coses son bestieses. Vaig neixer en una familia de classe mitjana bastant preocupada per la meva educacio. Vaig anar a escoles concertades i privades, fins que vaig acabar a la universitat, on vaig estudiar traduccio i interpretacio. Vaig fer dues practiques unes a Catalunya, a la Sindicatura de Comptes de la Generalitat, i les altres a Austria, a l'Organisme Internacional d'Energia Atomica. Despres d'aquestes experiencies podem dir que gairebe laborals vaig patir una greu depressio a causa de la qual vaig haver de ser ingressada a l'Hospital de Sant Pau i de la Santa Creu de Barcelona, que em va salvar la vida. Sempre els ho agraire. Despres d'aquest entrebanc vaig decidir-me a estudiar un Master en Dret internacional, la qual cosa es una bogeria, tenint en compte que m'estava recuperant i que no es la meva materia. Pero podem dir que me'n vaig sortir prou be. 

 Ara que us he donat les meves dades biografiques a grans trets (basicament des del punt de vista professional, vaja) vull explicar-vos una mica mes sobre qui soc. Soc una noia bastant blanca de pell, d'estatura mitjana i bastant prima per la meva altura. De tota manera tambe es pot dir que soc voluptuosa, no soc pas recta. Tinc la cara mes aviat allargada, el front ample, els ulls grans i de color marro. El nas es mes aviat gros, una micona d'aliga. El meu pare diu que es un nas roma. Tinc les dents perfectament rectes en un somriure bastant bonic tot gracies a les meravelles de l'ortodoncia. Pel que fa a la resta del cos, puc destacar que tinc unes mans bastant boniques, una cintura ben petitona, el ventre relativament pla i les cames bastant llargues.

 Molt be, molt be, direu. Ens es igual el fisic. L'important es l'interior. Bajanades. Tothom diu aixo pero ningu no s'ho acaba de creure. De tota manera, tambe us penso explicar com soc, com a persona. M'agrada pensar que soc una persona amb principis, lleial als meus amics, honesta, exigent amb mi mateixa, treballadora, ambiciosa, comprensiva... Segurament dec semblar una creguda pero m'es bastant igual. M'agrada fer riure a la gent, fer-los sentir comodes al meu costat, fer-la petar, anar a caminar, cantar, maquillar-me, llegir i escriure, de vegades dibuixar... No tinc molts amics, pero els que tinc valen molt.





'
